entries.femaleVariant: Whaddup, Night City! We've got a special guest on today's episode of "Chip In" – the center for the Night City Blackouts, Kevin King! Super-psyched to have you here, Mr. King.
All right, Kev, how's the mood right before the playoffs? Give us your inside scoop.
Trust me, girl, the hype is REAL this time, yo.
Don't doubt it... So word through the grapevine's that your newest sponsor, BioDyne, chipped you their latest implant  – the Cubit-2.
Get the job done?! Girl, I jump around like a flea with these babies!
Last game I dropped fifty-three points, got twenty-four boards and thirty-two assists. Would've never even gotten close without 'em!
Hahahaha! You kiddin'? I got my whole family on these. Even my gramps!
Ladies and chooms, the Cubit-2 from BioDyne approved by Kevin King himself – available tomorrow in authorized retailers! See ya soon, and keep on chippin' in!
That's right. Oh, and a shout-out to All Foods. Great food, great life.
So about those implants? They get the job done?
